An Administration Police officer accused of killing his colleague at the residence of National Assembly Speaker Justin Muturi has denied the allegation.John Githinji yesterday recorded a statement with Gigiri DCI officers and denied attacking Dismas Masitsa. He said they were ambushed by criminals.Githinji said he was asleep in the police guardroom when he heard gunshots and realised Masitsa had been shot thrice.Detectives will present the officer before a magistrate today to seek more time to probe the murder. The investigators have taken the officers&rsquo; guns for ballistic examination to ascertain where the killer shots were fired from.